in absolute numbers. Usability heuristics relating to exits and user errors were more
difficult to apply than the rest, and additional measures should be taken to find
problems relating to these heuristics. Usability problems that relate to missing interface
elements that ought to be introduced were more difficult to find by heuristic evaluation
in interfaces implemented as paper prototypes but were as easy as other problems to
find in running systems.},
